================================================================================
Models
================================================================================

This project does NOT bundle or redistribute any model weights. Models are
downloaded at runtime from their original sources (Hugging Face), each under
its own license. The default model stack is fully permissive (Apache-2.0):

Speech recognition (ASR) — pick one in the popup:
  * IBM Granite Speech 4.1 2B   (ibm-granite/granite-speech-4.1-2b)   Apache-2.0
  * Qwen3-ASR 1.7B              (Qwen/Qwen3-ASR-1.7B)                  Apache-2.0
  * Qwen3-ASR 0.6B              (Qwen/Qwen3-ASR-0.6B)                  Apache-2.0  [lite]
  * (power-user) Parakeet TDT 0.6B v2 via sherpa-onnx                 CC-BY-4.0 (model)

Translation / summarization — Gemma 4 (Google), all Apache-2.0.
Tiered so the project runs across a range of hardware:

  tier   model (Apple Silicon / MLX)                weights (q4)  use
  -----  ----------------------------------------   -----------   --------------------
  full   mlx-community/gemma-4-26b-a4b-it-4bit       ~14 GB        best quality (32GB)
  mid    mlx-community/gemma-4-e4b-it-4bit          ~5  GB        balanced  (16GB)
  lite   mlx-community/gemma-4-e2b-it-4bit (qat)     ~3.2 GB       minimal   (<=16GB)

  Windows + NVIDIA (llama.cpp GGUF):
  full   google/gemma-4-26B-A4B-it-qat-q4_0-gguf
  mid    google/gemma-4-E4B-it-qat-q4_0-gguf
  lite   google/gemma-4-E2B-it-qat-q4_0-gguf

Gemma 4 is released by Google under the Apache License 2.0. Earlier Gemma
releases (1/2/3) used the separate "Gemma Terms of Use"; this project targets
Gemma 4 specifically and does not depend on those terms.

